 Précis the ideal text for students and teachers of translation, of English as a second language, and of all types of English Composition. It is intended for use in universities, community colleges, high schools, and in adult education. The exercises have been carefully chosen and organized so as to provide optimum hands-on learning experience for the reader; they vary in difficulty, so that the teacher may select those that suit the level of proficiency and the special interests of a particular group of students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAbstractingvProblems, exercises, etc. 0aAbstractingxProblems, exercises, etc. 0aAbstracting. 0aResumes analytiquesxRedactionxProblemes et exercices. 0aResumes analytiquesxRedaction. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780776608983?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780776608983423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780776608983/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles